The '''Detroit Regional LGBT Chamber of Commerce''' (@LGBTchamber) is a U.S. [[not-for-profit]] [[advocacy group]] that aims to expand the economic opportunities and advancement of the [[LGBT]] business community in Southeast [[Michigan]]. Its headquarters are in [[Detroit]]. The chamber is an affiliate of the exclusive certifying body for LGBT-owned businesses known as LGBT Business Enterprises (LGBTBEs).<ref>{{Cite news |author = BTL Staff |url = https://pridesource.com/article/77939-2/ |title = Wells Fargo and NGLCC Award $2,500 to Detroit Regional LGBT Chamber of Commerce |date = September 1, 2016 |work = Pridesource |access-date = July 24, 2018 |language = en-US }}</ref> Since its inception, it was an advocate for the inclusion of LGBT identities at the national level to replace just lesbian and gay.<ref>{{Cite news |first = Michael K. |last = Lavers |url = http://www.washingtonblade.com/2017/11/18/nglcc-changes-name-national-lgbt-chamber-commerce/ |title = NGLCC changes name to National LGBT Chamber of Commerce |date = November 18, 2017 |work = Washington Blade |access-date = November 20, 2017 |language = en-US }}</ref> In 2015, the LGBT Chamber was the first in the world to establish pride night games at all four [[major professional sports leagues in the United States and Canada]] under then CEO [[James Felton Keith]].<ref>{{Cite news |author = SI Wire |url = https://www.si.com/nfl/2015/06/30/detroit-lions-gay-lgbt-pride-night |title = Lions to host LGBT pride night in October |date = June 30, 2015 |work = [[Sports Illustrated]] |access-date = July 24, 2018 |language = en-US }}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news |first = Dave |last = Birkett |url = https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2015/06/29/detroit-lions-lgbt-pride-night/29478141/ |title = LGBT pride event slated for Lions game this fall |date = June 29, 2015 |work = [[Detroit Free Press]] |access-date = July 24, 2018 |language = en-US }}</ref>
